----------------------------------------------------------------------

This is a fork of mozilla-ai/tinyagent (HEAD e667858a, Apache-2.0). Material
modifications:

  - Single-file packaging (no `src/` directory; `tinyagent.py` at repo root).
  - Callback hook surface collapsed to the canonical 5-hook set
    (before_llm_call, after_llm_call, before_tool_execution,
    after_tool_execution, on_error), removing the upstream agent-level
    brackets and replacing them with the spec-required on_error hook.
  - MCP transports restricted to stdio; SSE and Streamable HTTP branches
    dropped entirely (user spec, locked decision #3).
  - `gen_ai.usage.cost` custom span attribute (USD, total) on top of the
    standardized `gen_ai.usage.input_tokens` / `output_tokens`.
  - Built-in `calculate` tool uses `simpleeval` instead of raw `eval`.
  - OpenTelemetry wiring follows the library pattern (no exporter wiring,
    no `set_tracer_provider` call in this package; host application
    configures the provider).

The fork retains every Apache-2.0 §4(a)-(d) obligation: a verbatim copy of
the upstream LICENSE in this directory, prominent change notices in
modified source files (see the SPDX headers at the top of `tinyagent.py`),
